        <p> I got ready and packed my things. Got me a few more bottles of water and ordered me a taxi to the Cebu South Bus Terminal bus station. A bus with a running air conditioning system was already ready to get in there. I had my luggage stowed away and looked for a place. During the rest of the waiting time, flying dealers came on the bus every few seconds and tried to get rid of their goods. From burgers, fries, nuts, donuts to cookies to Ray ben sunglasses. </p>
        <p> Steffi asked me the days whether there is a toilet on board the bus. I can only deny this. Didn't find any. The bus stopped twice on the way for a Pipi break. The toilets were even very clean and freshly wiped. ;) </p>
        <p> After 7 hours of ride including a ferry, I was finally in Cebu. There the bus driver put me completely in the wrong place. Oh well. Occurs. So caught stuff and off in the opposite direction. After just a few seconds, a tricycle (Tryk) stopped next to me and the driver looked at me questioningly. </p>
